[2]
Date: 27 Mar 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Regions.ru, 27 Mar 2004 [translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.regions.ru/newsheadlines/index.html?section=news&topic=health>

25 people intoxicated with white phosphorus are currently in the Stavropol
hospital (Russia)
-------------------------------------------------
There are still 25 people hospitalized with white phosphorus intoxication
in Stavropol hospitals. According to information from the regional
emergency center, altogether 77 people were admitted to the hospital with
this diagnosis, 49 of them being treated in the outpatient department.
The iron container containing white phosphorus was discovered on the
grounds of the Stavropol railway station in January 2004. On 21 Mar, as a
result of breakage of the container and the effects of sunlight, 50 kg of
the toxic substance was ejected into the 70 square meter territory, with
further ignition.
Work is presently being done to decontaminate the soil in the area.
According to sanitary epidemiological surveillance center specialists, the
levels of phosphoranhydride are within safe ranges.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[White phosphorus burns when exposed to air. If tissue is exposed to it, it
produces a painful burning sensation. The white phosphorus can be removed
underwater, which would also prevent the spontaneous fires. Treating
patients who have ingested the substance is much more difficult and may
prove unrewarding. - Mod.TG]
